article.headline: W. Illinois 63, Quincy 0
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. (AP) -- Running back Herb Donaldson rushed for three touchdowns in the first quarter to lead Western Illinois to a 63-0 rout over Quincy on Saturday. Western Illinois (1-1 Missouri Valley Conference) scored on each of its first six drives. Quincy (0-1 Great Lakes Valley Conference) didn't force the Leathernecks to punt until the Hawks were down 42-0 in the second quarter. Senior Leatherneck kicker Taylor Rowan was put to work Saturday, kicking field goals after all nine Western Illinois touchdowns. Western Illinois had more than 400 yards rushing. The Leathernecks also had 172 yards passing, to make for nearly 600 yards of offense. The Leatherneck defense held the Hawks to just under 150 yards of offense. Western Illinois quarterback Matt Barr had 151 yards and two touchdowns for the night. Donaldson finished with 128 yards, three touchown on 15 carries. Western Illinois had 25 first downs while Quincy had 11. Quincy quarterback Sam Donatucci had two interceptions in his college debut and went 12-of-26. Corey Williams led Quincy with 84 rushing yards on 11 carries. The victory was Western Illinois' 15th straight home-opening win.
